cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on dialogue research and natural language processing in a fantasy game environment. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses training goal-oriented models with reinforcement learning. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses reinforcement learning and imitation learning to train the models. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the interaction between agents and humans in a game environment. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of top-K utterances from a chit-chat model to inform the policy of the goal-oriented model.
